  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Electrical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Electrical Engineer (TWRP – C2A Influent Pumping Stations)</strong></u></p><h2>Job Description</h2><ul><li><p>Coordinate and supervise electrical works for the <strong>Tuas Water Reclamation Plant (TWRP), C2A – Influent Pumping Stations project</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Review electrical drawings, method statements and material submissions.</p></li><li><p>Monitor site installation, testing and commissioning of electrical systems including <strong>LV power distribution, switchboards, MCCs and control panels</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with consultants, subcontractors and project teams to resolve technical issues.</p></li><li><p>Conduct site inspections and ensure works comply with approved specifications, PUB requirements and safety regulations.</p></li><li><p>Prepare progress reports, inspection records and as-built documentation.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with <strong>Workplace Safety and Health (WSH)</strong> requirements.<br /></p></li></ul><h2>Job Requirements</h2><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Electrical Engineering</strong> or related field.</p></li><li><p><strong>2–5 years of relevant experience</strong> in electrical works for infrastructure, water treatment, wastewater treatment or industrial projects.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with <strong>Singapore electrical codes, PUB requirements</strong> and site practices.</p></li><li><p>Able to interpret electrical drawings and specifications.</p></li><li><p>Good coordination and communication skills.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in MS Office; AutoCAD knowledge is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Willing to work on site at <strong>Tuas</strong>.</p></li></ul>",
